nix-shell
zig build run
zig build --watch -fincremental

also

zig build db
zig build model

ONNX Runtime scaffold (YOLO integration path):

- ONNX Runtime is always enabled in build.
- If headers/libs are not in default toolchain paths, pass:
  - `-Donnx-include=/path/to/include`
  - `-Donnx-lib=/path/to/lib`
- If unset, build tries to resolve paths via Nix:
  - `nixpkgs#onnxruntime.dev.outPath`
  - `nixpkgs#onnxruntime.outPath`
- Download default model to `zig-out/bin/model.onnx`:
  - `zig build model`
  - optional custom URL: `zig build model -Dmodel-url=https://.../model.onnx`
- Model path is resolved automatically as `<selfExeDir>/model.onnx`, so with current build steps:
  - `zig build run`
- YOLO post-processing lives in `yolo.zig` (decode + NMS); it is included in `zig build test`.
- Image tensor preprocessing lives in `image_preprocess.zig` (RGB u8 -> NCHW f32), also covered by `zig build test`.
- Upload inference decodes common image formats (PNG/JPEG/etc via `zigimg`) in `image_decode.zig` before preprocessing/running ONNX, with PPM(P6) fallback.
- Output shape inference supports both common YOLO layouts: `[1,8400,84]` and `[1,84,8400]`.
